text: Which of the following driver's equipment can be used during the competition?

answer_options.answer_text: A helmet with the certification FIA 8860-2010 with insignificant scratches and multiple stickers of competitions going back to 2015
A suit with the standard SFI 3.2A/5 which has a manufacturing defect which has been covered with a sponsor's logo made from regular cotton
Shoes with the standard FIA Standard 8856-2000 without a FIA hologram label on it.
A frontal head restraint system which has no label, that has probably been supplied together with a helmet certified according to FIA 8860-2004
A helmet with the certification SFI 31.1/2010 which is in pristine condition and has been properly stored

text: What is incorrect regarding the brake system?

answer_options.answer_text: The brake pedal must be able to hold up even when the strongest officials are pressing the brake pedal by foot as intended
The brake system can be split diagonally into two independent hydraulic circuits - one for the front-left and rear-right wheel and one for the front-right and rear-left wheel
Regenerative braking is not possible in a vehicle with combustion engine
The brake disk may be attached by clamping between the hub and the wheel, using the wheel lug bolts as the fasteners
The function of the BOTS may be tested after the endurance by opening a bleed valve at one of the brake calipers. If the BOTS is not triggered during this test, this will result in a DQ
